<node TEXT="&#xf0b7;&#xf020;&#xf020; basic Standard American, a 2&#xf0a7; system, but where an opening of 1 of a major&#xa;    promises 5 cards, and where 1NT is always strong (16-18).[file name: &quot;f-amc-b&quot;]&#xa;&#xa;&#xf0b7;&#xf020;&#xf020; Standard American Yellow Card, is similar to basic Standard American,&#xa;    but the 1NT opening range is one point lower (15-17), and more conventions&#xa;    are used. This system is used with Internet bridge clubs. [file name: &quot;f-sayc-i&quot;]&#xa;&#xa;&#xf0b7;&#xf020;&#xf020; 2-over-1 game forcing, is similar to advanced Standard American Yellow Card&#xa;    but a response at the two level, like 2&#xf0a8; over 1&#xf0aa;, forces to game (and needs therefore&#xa;    a stronger hand). [file name: &quot;f-2-1-a&quot;]" ID="ID_1265307864" CREATED="1681496279489" MODIFIED="1681496317401"/>
</node>
