<node TEXT="In defence, cards often have conventional meanings, like showing count&#xa;or attitude. You get the meaning of the cards which possibly can be played,&#xa;by clicking first&#xa;&#x2022; at the start of the play, when it is your turn to lead: on the button List;&#xa;&#x2022; later in the play: on the button Evaluate,&#xa;  then the check: Conventional meaning, followed by Ok.&#xa;&#xa;When you want to see the conventional meaning of cards already played:&#xa;&#x2022; Click on the button Evaluate;&#xa;&#x2022; if you want to know the meaning of cards played by North:&#xa;   check the cross of &#x201c;ask who&#x201d; = South and &#x201c;ask about&#x201d; = North;&#xa;&#x2022; click on Ok." ID="ID_89886732" CREATED="1681497366341" MODIFIED="1681497373821"/>
<node TEXT="like bcalcgui" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1020245734" CREATED="1681497410742" MODIFIED="1681497417670">
<node TEXT="clicking on the button List or Evaluate, then either on&#xa;    Expected tricks with hidden hands&#xa;or&#xa;    Expected tricks with open hands&#xa;&#xa;In the first case, for its calculation, the program only uses &#x201c;legal&#x201d; knowledge&#xa;about the hidden hands as available from the bidding and the play so far,&#xa;whereas in the second case the calculation is done with the full knowledge&#xa;of all hands (&#x201c;double dummy play&#x201d;)." ID="ID_999216458" CREATED="1681497417700" MODIFIED="1681497425581"/>
</node>
